profile_positions.description:
Leading the Data Foundation area with more than 90 engineers. I oversee the whole development lifecycle, from concept to deployment, including architectural decisions and business alignment. Currently, my main responsibilities at ING involve:
- Development of Data Warehouse for  the Finance and Risk data using PostgreSQL hosted on Microsoft Azure
- Development of data integration platform for the Finance and Risk domain with these characteristics: 100% open source based; full CI/CD pipeline; cloud based; event-driven OLRT solution with no scheduling; 
- Operational support for daily processing of financial transactions within the scope of Financial Markets and Commercial Banking;
- Operational support for identity and access management;
- Managerial activities including budget control, strategic roadmaps, people (internal and offshore strategies) and career guidance.

I lead a team of Data Scientists using the most innovative and solution-driven technologies to guide all areas of PagSeguro. We give data driven insights in a fast-paced hyper-growth environment, to disrupt the payment industry in Brazil and to foster social inclusion thru our solutions.

My daily activities involve:

- motivating and coaching a group of high skilled individuals working in multidisciplinary data science projects;
- review and inspect team's deliveries to leverage insights that are relevant to our business. Further, ensure the hypothesis which upon our projects are based adhere to PagSeguro strategy;
- coach the team regarding data science and deep/machine learning issues (algorithms, programming (R, Python, SQL), business modelling);
- help build a data driven organization.
